sational encounters in everyday interactions in which participants offer different interpretations of the hidden meaning the words carry. Marsilli-Vargas does not analyze these interpretations as impositions or interruptions but as productive exchanges. By outlining how psychoanalytic listening operates as a genre, Marsilli-Vargas opens up ways to imagine other modes of listening and forms of social interaction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aInterpersonal communication and culturezArgentinazBuenos Aires. 0aListeningxPsychological aspects. 0aListeningxSocial aspects. 0aPsychoanalysisxMethodology. 0aPsychoanalysisxSocial aspectszArgentinazBuenos Aires. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023159?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023159423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023159/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles